Solutum cumulus mediocris
=========================
Files and slides from my Blackhat Asia 2014 presentation.
This repository contains the following files:

 * returnbrute.pl
   PoC how you can brute force hidden validation pages in APIs where the
   payment gateway makes a HTTP request to the merchant to validate payment
   received. If you know the url you can usually spoof this message
 * Dynamic.conf
   Example of how a payment gateway request validation digest can be defined
   as a dynamic format for cracking with john the ripper
 * html2dynamic.pl
   Extract values from the checkout html form to generate a dynamic hash to
   be cracked with john the ripper
 * Solutum cumulus mediocris
   Presentation slides (with annotations)
